          By the same sets of criteria described above for
          studying the difference between wild-type and 
          actA infections, we examined
          whether there were any <ENAMEX TYPE="SUBSTANCE">genes</ENAMEX> reproducibly induced by
          cytoplasmic <ENAMEX TYPE="SUBSTANCE">bacteria</ENAMEX> (wild-type or 
