          passed these criteria during <TIMEX TYPE="TIME">the first 4 hours</TIMEX> of
          infection. It is likely that differences in the
          transcriptional program would emerge at <TIMEX TYPE="TIME">later</TIMEX> stages of
          infection, as wild-type and 
          actA <ENAMEX TYPE="SUBSTANCE">bacteria replicate</ENAMEX> and kill
