          Surprisingly, the apical surface appeared to be most
          sensitive to the presence of <ENAMEX TYPE="SUBSTANCE">bacteria</ENAMEX>, but this could be
          explained by the fact that the membrane supporting the
          basolateral cell surface reduced the amount of surface
          area available for <ENAMEX TYPE="SUBSTANCE">receptor</ENAMEX> expression. It is also
          possible that a very small amount of lipotechoic acid
